        "The Zomato Data Analysis Project focuses on exploring and analyzing restaurant data to understand customer preferences, restaurant performance, and various factors that influence ratings and popularity. Zomato is a popular online platform that allows users to discover restaurants, read reviews, check menus, and rate their dining experiences. With the rapid growth of online food delivery services, analyzing restaurant data has become important for understanding market trends and improving customer satisfaction. This project uses the Zomato dataset to perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) using Python and data analysis libraries.\n",
        "\n",
        "The main objective of this project is to examine the available restaurant data and identify meaningful patterns and insights. The dataset contains information such as restaurant names, cuisines, ratings, number of reviews, and cost details. By analyzing these attributes, we can understand which restaurants perform better, which cuisines are most popular, and how pricing may influence customer ratings. The project also helps in understanding customer behavior based on reviews and ratings.\n",
        "\n",
        "The first step in the project is data collection and loading. The Zomato dataset is imported into the analysis environment using Pandas, a powerful Python library for data manipulation and analysis. The dataset is loaded into a DataFrame where the rows represent restaurants and the columns represent different attributes such as ratings, cuisines, and costs. Once the data is loaded, the structure of the dataset is examined to understand the available columns and the type of information present in each field.\n",
        "\n",
        "The next step is data cleaning and preprocessing. Real-world datasets often contain missing values, duplicate records, or inconsistent formats. In this project, missing ratings or incomplete records are identified and handled appropriately. The ratings column is converted into numeric format to ensure proper calculations. Cleaning the dataset is an important step because accurate analysis depends on high-quality data.\n",
        "\n",
        "After cleaning the data, the project proceeds to exploratory data analysis (EDA). EDA is used to summarize the dataset and visualize patterns through graphs and statistical measures. Various techniques are used to analyze the data, such as calculating average ratings, identifying the most reviewed restaurants, and examining the distribution of ratings. Visualization libraries like Matplotlib and Seaborn are used to create graphs and charts that help in understanding the data more effectively.\n",
        "\n",
